'''Olwethu Mpilwenhle Makhanya''' (born 30 April 2004) is a South African professional [[Association football|soccer]] player who plays as a [[Defender (association football)|defender]] for the [[Philadelphia Union]] of [[Major League Soccer]] and the [[South Africa national soccer team|South Africa national team]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.snl24.com/soccerladuma/local/sa-players-abroad/makhanya-the-anticipation-was-killing-me-20230808|title=Makhanya: The Anticipation Was Killing Me|publisher=snl24.com}}</ref>

==Career==

Makhanya started his career with South African side [[Stellenbosch F.C.|Stellenbosch]], where he was regarded to have performed well for the club.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.sowetanlive.co.za/sport/soccer/2023-07-18-stellies-proud-to-release-makhanya-to-us-league-club/|title=Stellies proud to release Makhanya|publisher=sowetanlive.co.za}}</ref> He was nominated for South Africa Young Footballer of the Year.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.snl24.com/soccerladuma/fan-park/what-could-olwethu-makhanya-bring-to-mamelodi-sundowns-20230621|title=What could Olwethu Makhanya offer at Downs?|publisher=snl24.com}}</ref> He won the [[2022-23 Nedbank Cup]] Most Promising Player award.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.snl24.com/soccerladuma/local/sa-players-abroad/olwethu-makhanya-how-i-got-signed-by-philadelphia-union-20230723|title=Makhanya: How Philadelphia Scouted Me In SA|publisher=Soccer Laduma}}</ref> In 2023, he signed for American side [[Philadelphia Union]], becoming the club's first under-22 initiative signing.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.sabcsport.com/soccer/news/olwethu-makhanyas-special-mls-status-explained|title=Olwethu Makhanya's special MLS status explained|publisher=sabcsport.com}}</ref>

==Style of play==

Makhanya is known for his bravery.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.timeslive.co.za/sport/soccer/2023-07-01-young-players-who-need-to-play-their-last-season-in-the-psl-and-move-overseas/|title=Olwethu Makhanya - Times Live article}}</ref> He can operate as a central defender in a back four or a back three.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.snl24.com/kickoff/sanews/sa-players-abroad/philadelphia-union-director-opens-on-signing-explosive-makhanya-20230720|title=Philadelphia Union director opens up on signing 'explosive' Makhanya|publisher=Kick Off}}</ref>

==Personal life==

Makhanya has regarded England international [[John Stones]] as one of his soccer idols.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://947.co.za/articles/2023/07/20/former-stellenbosch-fc-star-olwethu-makhanya-living-the-american-dream-in-mls|title=Olwethu Makhanya living the American dream in MLS|publisher=947.co.za}}</ref>

